title: Adenoma patient 125
treatment_protocol_ch1: Tissue was collected at the time of surgery and preserved in RNAlater (Ambion, Austin, TX) within one minute of collection. Linear polyacrylamide (5 ul) was added to ~50 mg of tumor sample and homogenization was carried out on ice in 1.5 ml Trizol (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) with a polytron homogenizer for 30 seconds.
growth_protocol_ch1: A set of 43 ovarian tumors was obtained from the Ovarian Cancer Institute (Atlanta).  Tissue was collected at the time of surgery and preserved in RNAlater (Ambion, Austin, TX) within one minute of collection.
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was isolated from crude homogenate according to the manufacturer’s protocols (Trizol) and further enriched using an RNEasy column (Qiagen, Valencia, CA).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol from 6 ug total RNA (Expression Analysis Technical Manual, 2001, Affymetrix).
hyb_protocol: Following fragmentation, 10 ug of cRNA were hybridized for 16 hr at 45C on GeneChip Drosophila Genome Array. GeneChips were washed and stained in the Affymetrix Fluidics Station 400.
scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using GeneArray Scanner Model G2500
description: Gene expression data from ovarian adenoma.
data_processing: The data were analyzed using GCRMA normalization with GeneTraffic Software (Iobion, La Jolla, CA).
